WHEN Andile Jali was not getting any game time at Mamelodi Sundowns shortly after joining, he was trolled constantly on social media. The former Orlando Pirates midfielder, though, appears to be having the last laugh. He has fought his way into the Downs team in recent months and is arguably one of the first names on coach Pitso Mosimane's team-sheet. But Jali has not forgotten about what he went through during his days on the sidelines. He took to social media to hit back at some of his detractors through a series of tweets.          